By Joy Akinsanya Abeokuta – The police on Friday arraigned two men in a Chief Magistrates’ Court sitting in Isabo, Abeokuta, for allegedly stealing N77 million belonging to their employer. The police charged Adeyinka Usman, 35 and Obamoyegun Tosin, 32, of no fixed address with two counts of conspiracy and stealing. The prosecutor, Insp. Bukola Abolade told the court that the accused
committed the offence between January and August 2018 at the Green
legacy resort, Oke Mosan in Abeokuta. Abolade said the accused and others still at large, who were
employees at the resort, allegedly conspired and stole N77 million
through the use of POS machine. She added that the money stolen was a property of Green Legacy
Resort, a branch under the Olusegun Obasanjo Presidential Library (OOPL)
in Oke Mosan Abeokuta. The prosecutor, said the offence, contravened the provisions of
Sections 390(9) and 516 of the Criminal Code Laws of Ogun state 2006. The accused, however, pleaded not guilty to the counts when it was read to them. The Magistrate O.O Odubanjo admitted the accused to bail in the sum of N2million each with two sureties in like sum. She ordered that the sureties must own a developed landed property
and must also provide evidence of tax payment to Ogun government.  She adjourned the case until Feb. 12 for hearing. (NAN)